@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Honda Shine vs Hero Splendor: Full 2025 Comparison Guide";
}
@section MetaTags {
    <meta name="keywords" content="Honda Shine vs Hero Splendor, Shine vs Splendor comparison 2025, Honda Shine 125 mileage, Hero Splendor Plus features 2025, Best commuter bike in India 2025, Shine vs Splendor performance, Splendor Plus mileage comparison, Honda Shine specifications, Hero Splendor specifications, Shine vs Splendor which is better, 100cc vs 125cc bike comparison, Honda vs Hero review, Affordable bikes in India 2025, Best bike for daily commute 2025" />
    <meta name="description" content="Compare Honda Shine 125 vs Hero Splendor Plus in 2025. Check mileage, features, price, performance and decide which commuter bike is best for your needs." />
}

@functions {
    public string Truncate(string input, int length)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input) || input.Length <= length)
            return input;
        return input.Substring(0, length) + "...";
    }
}
<body id="bg">
    @* <div class="header-img"><img src="~/images/main-slider/header.png" alt="bikecarhubheaderimage" title="bikecarhubheaderimage" /></div> *@
    <div class="m-t90">
        <div><h1 class="latest-bike-head">@Model.BlogHeading</h1></div>
        <div class=" latest-bike-container">
            @* <div style="background-image:url(@ViewBag.TWNews.ImageURL);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position: center;background-size:contain ;height: 400px;box-shadow: 5px 10px 8px #888888;border-radius:10px;background-color:#ebecee;padding:60px;"></div> *@
            <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-image">
                <img src="@Model.ImageURL" alt="@Model.BlogHeading" title="@Model.BlogHeading" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='@Url.Content("~/images/default.jpg")';" />
                <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-text">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> @Model.Date?.ToString("d MMM yyyy")</p>
                    @* <p>@ViewBag.TWNews.NewsSummary</p> *@
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Written by:</span> BikeCarHub Editorial Team</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Published on:</span> 3rd July 2025</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Introduction</h2>

                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                   <p>But if you're planning to buy a bike in 2025, you might be wondering -- which one is better: Honda Shine or Hero Splendor?</p>
                <p>In this detailed comparison by <span class="font-weight-700"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">BikeCarHub</a></span>, we will break down every important aspect like engine performance, mileage, features, pricing, and more to help you decide which bike suits you best in 2025.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Overview of the Bikes</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Hero" asp-action="HeroSplendorPlus">Hero Splendor+</a></h3>
                <p>A 100cc icon with a reputation for durability, simplicity, and top-tier mileage. The Splendor+ has been updated for 2025 with BS6-2.0 compliance while maintaining its core values of affordability and reliability.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Honda" asp-action="HondaShine125">Honda Shine 125</a></h3>
                <p>A refined 125cc bike offering more power, style, and Honda's reliable engine technology. The 2025 model comes with improved features while retaining its comfortable ride quality.</p>

                <p>Both bikes have been updated over the years and remain best-sellers in their segments.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Engine & Performance</h2>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Specification</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Hero Splendor+</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Honda Shine 125</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Engine Capacity</td>
                                <td>97.2cc, Air-cooled</td>
                                <td>123.94cc, Air-cooled</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Max Power</td>
                                <td>5.9 kW@8000 rpm</td>
                                <td>7.93 kW@7500 rpm</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Max Torque</td>
                                <td>8.05 Nm@6000 RPM</td>
                                <td>11 Nm@6000 RPM</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Gearbox</td>
                                <td>4-speed manual</td>
                                <td>5-speed manual</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Battery</td>
                                <td>MF Battery, 12V - 3Ah</td>
                                <td>12V, 5Ah</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Emission Type</td>
                                <td>BS6-2.0</td>
                                <td>BS6-2.0</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Top Speed</td>
                                <td>87 kmph</td>
                                <td>90 kmph</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Hero Splendor+</span> is built for city commuting with moderate power and smooth pickup. Its 97.2cc engine is tuned for efficiency rather than performance.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Honda Shine</span> offers more torque and power from its 125cc engine, making it suitable for both city and occasional highway rides. The extra gear (5-speed vs 4-speed) also helps in highway cruising.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Shine wins for performance. Splendor is sufficient for basic daily rides.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Mileage & Fuel Efficiency</h2>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Bike</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Claimed Mileage</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Hero Splendor+</td>
                                <td>70 km/l</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Honda Shine 125</td>
                                <td>55 km/l</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Hero Splendor+</span> offers best-in-class mileage, ideal for cost-conscious users who prioritize fuel efficiency above all else.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Honda Shine</span> is also efficient but burns slightly more fuel due to its larger engine. The trade-off comes in the form of better performance.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Hero Splendor is the clear mileage king.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Features & Comfort</h2>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Feature</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Hero Splendor+</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Honda Shine 125</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>i3S (Start-Stop)</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                                <td>❌ No</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Digital Meter</td>
                                <td>❌ No</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes (in Shine Smart)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Silent Start (ACG motor)</td>
                                <td>❌ No</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Tubeless Tyres</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Combined Braking System</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>USB Charging</td>
                                <td>❌ No</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Additional Features</td>
                                <td>XSENS Advantage Technology</td>
                                <td>Eco Indicator, Silent Start with ACG</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Kill Switch</td>
                                <td>❌ No</td>
                                <td>✅ Yes</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Honda Shine</span> offers a smoother ride and comes with modern features like ACG motor (silent start) and optional semi-digital cluster in Smart variant. The addition of a USB charging port is useful for smartphone users.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Hero Splendor+</span> keeps it simple but practical with i3S for fuel-saving during stop-and-go traffic. The XSENS technology helps with efficient fuel injection.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Shine wins for comfort and features, especially for daily riders who appreciate modern conveniences.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Price Comparison (Ex-showroom Delhi)</h2>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Variant</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Price (Approx)</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Hero Splendor+ Drum</td>
                                <td>₹75,000 -- ₹80,000</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Hero Splendor+ i3S Drum</td>
                                <td>₹78,426</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Honda Shine Drum</td>
                                <td>₹85,021</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Honda Shine Disc</td>
                                <td>₹89,772</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p>The Hero Splendor+ is available in multiple variants with slight price variations based on features like i3S and color options. The Honda Shine comes in fewer variants but with more standard features.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Hero Splendor is more affordable, but Shine offers more value for slightly higher price.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Maintenance & Reliability</h2>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Hero Splendor+</span> wins in affordability and availability of spare parts, especially in rural areas. The simple mechanicals make it easy and inexpensive to maintain.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Honda Shine</span> has great long-term reliability and smoother engine performance but slightly higher service costs due to more complex features.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Both are reliable, but Splendor is cheaper to maintain.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Final Comparison Summary</h2>

                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Criteria</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Hero Splendor+</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Honda Shine 125</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Engine Power</td>
                                <td>97.2cc -- 8.02 PS</td>
                                <td>123.94cc -- 10.74 PS</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Mileage</td>
                                <td>70-75 km/l</td>
                                <td>60-65 km/l</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Comfort & Features</td>
                                <td>Basic</td>
                                <td>Modern & Smooth</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Ride Quality</td>
                                <td>City-focused</td>
                                <td>City + Short Highway</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Price Range</td>
                                <td>₹75K--₹80K</td>
                                <td>₹85K--₹90K</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Maintenance Cost</td>
                                <td>Very Low</td>
                                <td>Low</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Fuel Tank Capacity</td>
                                <td>9.8 Litre</td>
                                <td>10.5 Litre</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Kerb Weight</td>
                                <td>112 kg</td>
                                <td>113 kg</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Who Should Buy What?</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">✅ Buy Hero Splendor+ if:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>You want maximum mileage</li>
                    <li>Your commute is mostly short & inside the city</li>
                    <li>You want a low-maintenance, tried-and-tested bike</li>
                    <li>Budget is a top priority</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">✅ Buy Honda Shine if:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>You ride longer distances or want more comfort</li>
                    <li>You want a slightly powerful engine</li>
                    <li>You can spend a bit more for added features & refinement</li>
                    <li>You appreciate modern features like digital console and USB charging</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Conclusion - Shine vs Splendor in 2025</h2>

                <p>Both bikes are excellent and dominate India's commuter segment for a reason.</p>
                <p>👉 <span class="font-weight-700">Hero Splendor Plus</span> is best for those who want economy, reliability, and simplicity.</p>
                <p>👉 <span class="font-weight-700">Honda Shine</span> is ideal for those who want power, comfort, and modern features with decent mileage.</p>
                <p>In the end, it comes down to your budget, riding distance, and feature preferences. We recommend test riding both bikes before making your final decision.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
             
                <p></p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub</span> always recommends taking a test drive of both vehicles to feel the difference yourself before making a purchase.</p>
